ce:section.ce:para:
The real sample was mixed with the standard solution of Cr2O7
                        2− or vanillin for standard addition recovery experiments to evaluate the feasibility of the fluorescent sensor. Various concentrations of Cr2O7
                        2− were dissolved in the river water, and the recovery rate was 94.80 %-106.12 % by three repeated experiments (Table 1
                        ). Given that commercially available infant formula milk powder for 0–6 months does not contain vanillin, various amounts of vanillin standard solution and milk powder were mixed for detection. The corresponding recovery rate was 98.28 %-101.60 %, and the relative standard deviation was 1.12 %-3.41 % (Table 2
                        ).
